<paragraph blockId="9.[264,1323,470,1897]" pageId="9" pageNumber="42">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[264,418,470,496]" pageId="9" pageNumber="42">Description:</emphasis>
Shell small (maximum observed L= 
<number box="[860,911,471,497]" pageId="9" pageNumber="42" value="2.85">2.85</number>
, average= 
<number box="[1042,1079,471,497]" pageId="9" pageNumber="42" value="2.2">2.2</number>
± 
<number box="[1111,1166,471,497]" pageId="9" pageNumber="42" value="0.33">0.33</number>
), high (I H/L varying among localities between 
<number box="[684,713,511,537]" pageId="9" pageNumber="42" value="85.0">85</number>
± 
<number box="[753,768,511,537]" pageId="9" pageNumber="42" value="2.0">2</number>
and 
<number box="[834,886,511,537]" pageId="9" pageNumber="42" value="89.2">89.2</number>
<emphasis box="[897,913,511,536]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="42">±</emphasis>
<number box="[925,965,511,537]" pageId="9" pageNumber="42" value="2.3">2.3</number>
), inflated (Ci varying among localities between 
<number box="[490,519,551,577]" pageId="9" pageNumber="42" value="79.0">79</number>
± 
<number box="[558,573,551,577]" pageId="9" pageNumber="42" value="4.0">4</number>
and 
<number box="[637,688,551,577]" pageId="9" pageNumber="42" value="82.3">82.3</number>
<emphasis box="[700,716,551,576]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="42">±</emphasis>
<number box="[727,768,551,577]" pageId="9" pageNumber="42" value="4.6">4.6</number>
). Beaks wide at base, inflated and high, well visible over dorsal margin, sub-central or slightly displaced posteriorly (located at about 
<number box="[264,339,631,657]" pageId="9" pageNumber="42" value="58.5" valueMax="60.0" valueMin="57.0">57–60</number>
% of L). Shell outline trapezoid, anterior end slightly protruded, posterior end nearly straight, truncated. Dorsal margin short, markedly curve, ventral margin widely curve. Shell surface brilliant, white or yellowish, with somewhat regularly well marked commarginal striae (
<figureCitation box="[506,673,751,777]" captionStart="FIGURES 7 A – F" captionStartId="10.[264,382,1187,1211]" captionTargetBox="[264,1323,486,1162]" captionTargetId="figure@10.[264,1323,486,1162]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="FIGURES 7 A – F. Pisidium vile. A, B. Syntypes (ANSP 70489). A. Right valve, lateral view. B. Posterior view. C – F. Specimens from Arroyo Miguelín (MLP 5665). C. Posterolateral view, detail of escutcheon. D. Right valve, lateral view. E. Left valve, inner view. F. Right valve, inner view. Scale bars: A, B, D – F = 500 µm; C = 200 µm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/174354/files/figure.png" pageId="9" pageNumber="42">
Fig. 
<number box="[562,577,751,777]" pageId="9" pageNumber="42" value="7.0">7</number>
A, B, D
</figureCitation>
). Hinge plate solid (
<figureCitation box="[913,1037,751,777]" captionStart="FIGURES 7 A – F" captionStartId="10.[264,382,1187,1211]" captionTargetBox="[264,1323,486,1162]" captionTargetId="figure@10.[264,1323,486,1162]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="FIGURES 7 A – F. Pisidium vile. A, B. Syntypes (ANSP 70489). A. Right valve, lateral view. B. Posterior view. C – F. Specimens from Arroyo Miguelín (MLP 5665). C. Posterolateral view, detail of escutcheon. D. Right valve, lateral view. E. Left valve, inner view. F. Right valve, inner view. Scale bars: A, B, D – F = 500 µm; C = 200 µm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/174354/files/figure.png" pageId="9" pageNumber="42">
Fig. 
<number box="[969,984,751,777]" pageId="9" pageNumber="42" value="7.0">7</number>
E, F
</figureCitation>
). Hinge line moderately long (Hil/L varying among localities between 
<number box="[804,833,791,817]" pageId="9" pageNumber="42" value="56.0">56</number>
± 
<number box="[863,899,791,817]" pageId="9" pageNumber="42" value="1.6">1.6</number>
and 
<number box="[956,985,791,817]" pageId="9" pageNumber="42" value="58.0">58</number>
<emphasis box="[992,1008,791,816]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="42">±</emphasis>
<number box="[1015,1031,791,817]" pageId="9" pageNumber="42" value="3.0">3</number>
). Hinge: Left valve (
<figureCitation captionStart="FIGURES 7 A – F" captionStartId="10.[264,382,1187,1211]" captionTargetBox="[264,1323,486,1162]" captionTargetId="figure@10.[264,1323,486,1162]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="FIGURES 7 A – F. Pisidium vile. A, B. Syntypes (ANSP 70489). A. Right valve, lateral view. B. Posterior view. C – F. Specimens from Arroyo Miguelín (MLP 5665). C. Posterolateral view, detail of escutcheon. D. Right valve, lateral view. E. Left valve, inner view. F. Right valve, inner view. Scale bars: A, B, D – F = 500 µm; C = 200 µm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/174354/files/figure.png" pageId="9" pageNumber="42">
Fig. 
<number box="[264,280,831,857]" pageId="9" pageNumber="42" value="7.0">7</number>
E
</figureCitation>
): inner cardinal tooth (C 
<number box="[593,608,831,857]" pageId="9" pageNumber="42" value="2.0">2</number>
) robust, with pointed cusp bent upward, outer cardinal (C 
<number box="[1298,1314,831,857]" pageId="9" pageNumber="42" value="4.0">4</number>
) slender, curved, covering C 
<number box="[586,601,871,897]" pageId="9" pageNumber="42" value="2.0">2</number>
at posterior end; anterior (A 
<number box="[935,950,871,897]" pageId="9" pageNumber="42" value="2.0">2</number>
) and posterior (P 
<number box="[1154,1169,871,897]" pageId="9" pageNumber="42" value="2.0">2</number>
) lateral teeth robust with markedly displaced cusps. Right valve (
<figureCitation box="[884,975,911,937]" captionStart="FIGURES 7 A – F" captionStartId="10.[264,382,1187,1211]" captionTargetBox="[264,1323,486,1162]" captionTargetId="figure@10.[264,1323,486,1162]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="FIGURES 7 A – F. Pisidium vile. A, B. Syntypes (ANSP 70489). A. Right valve, lateral view. B. Posterior view. C – F. Specimens from Arroyo Miguelín (MLP 5665). C. Posterolateral view, detail of escutcheon. D. Right valve, lateral view. E. Left valve, inner view. F. Right valve, inner view. Scale bars: A, B, D – F = 500 µm; C = 200 µm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/174354/files/figure.png" pageId="9" pageNumber="42">
Fig. 
<number box="[940,956,911,937]" pageId="9" pageNumber="42" value="7.0">7</number>
F
</figureCitation>
): cardinal tooth (C 
<number box="[1201,1215,911,937]" pageId="9" pageNumber="42" value="3.0">3</number>
) minute, straight at anterior half, enlarged at posterior end in a triangular cup; inner anterior (A 
<number box="[1302,1312,951,977]" pageId="9" pageNumber="42" value="1.0">1</number>
) and inner posterior (A 
<number box="[533,544,991,1017]" pageId="9" pageNumber="42" value="1.0">1</number>
) laterals quite robust, outer lateral teeth (A 
<number box="[1065,1079,991,1017]" pageId="9" pageNumber="42" value="3.0">3</number>
, P 
<number box="[1111,1125,991,1017]" pageId="9" pageNumber="42" value="3.0">3</number>
) reduced in size but strong. Ligament pit enclosed, ligament slender, moderately long (Li= 
<number box="[1158,1187,1031,1057]" pageId="9" pageNumber="42" value="20.0">20</number>
± 
<number box="[1222,1262,1031,1057]" pageId="9" pageNumber="42" value="1.4">1.4</number>
), not visible from exterior. Escutcheon marked by a delicate line, anterior half slightly elevated, over the anterior half of ligament (
<figureCitation box="[668,760,1111,1137]" captionStart="FIGURES 7 A – F" captionStartId="10.[264,382,1187,1211]" captionTargetBox="[264,1323,486,1162]" captionTargetId="figure@10.[264,1323,486,1162]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="FIGURES 7 A – F. Pisidium vile. A, B. Syntypes (ANSP 70489). A. Right valve, lateral view. B. Posterior view. C – F. Specimens from Arroyo Miguelín (MLP 5665). C. Posterolateral view, detail of escutcheon. D. Right valve, lateral view. E. Left valve, inner view. F. Right valve, inner view. Scale bars: A, B, D – F = 500 µm; C = 200 µm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/174354/files/figure.png" pageId="9" pageNumber="42">
Fig. 
<number box="[723,739,1111,1137]" pageId="9" pageNumber="42" value="7.0">7</number>
C
</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="9.[264,1323,470,1897]" pageId="9" pageNumber="42">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[312,437,1150,1176]" pageId="9" pageNumber="42">Anatomy:</emphasis>
<emphasis box="[445,538,1151,1176]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="42">Mantle:</emphasis>
Only the anal mantle opening present, siphon retractor muscles of the same conditions as in 
<taxonomicName box="[568,810,1191,1216]" class="Bivalvia" family="Sphaeriidae" genus="Pisidium" kingdom="Animalia" order="Veneroida" pageId="9" pageNumber="42" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="sterkianum">
<emphasis box="[568,810,1191,1216]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="42">Pisidium sterkianum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName box="[868,1094,1191,1216]" class="Bivalvia" family="Sphaeriidae" genus="Pisidium" kingdom="Animalia" order="Veneroida" pageId="9" pageNumber="42" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="dorbignyi">
<emphasis box="[868,1094,1191,1216]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="42">Pisidium dorbignyi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<figureCitation box="[1110,1238,1191,1217]" captionStart="FIGURES 8 A – F" captionStartId="11.[264,382,1168,1192]" captionTargetBox="[315,1257,403,1149]" captionTargetId="figure@11.[302,1285,388,1178]" captionTargetPageId="11" captionText="FIGURES 8 A – F. Pisidium vile, anatomy. A, B. Lateral views of left (38) and right (39) inner mantle border showing siphonal and inner radial mantle muscles. C. Distribution of scars of inner radial mantle muscles. D. Inner view of inner demibranch showing position of developing brood sac. E. Left nephridium, dorsolateral view. F. Nephridia, dorsal view. (al: ascending lamellae; bs: brood sac; dl: descending lamellae; dln: dorsal lobe of nephridium; irm: inner radial mantle muscles; irms: scars of inner radial mantle muscles; ll: lateral loop of nephridium; pa: posterior adductor muscle; pl: pallial line; sr 1: anal siphon retractor; sr 2: retractor muscles corresponding to the lacking inhalant opening)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/174355/files/figure.png" pageId="9" pageNumber="42">
Fig. 
<number box="[1165,1179,1191,1217]" pageId="9" pageNumber="42" value="8.0">8</number>
A, B
</figureCitation>
). Inner radial mantle muscles forming six strong, well defined, bundles, evenly distributed along the pedal slit. Muscle scars well defined only in anterior part of the shell where they are separate from the mantle line (
<figureCitation box="[621,714,1311,1337]" captionStart="FIGURES 8 A – F" captionStartId="11.[264,382,1168,1192]" captionTargetBox="[315,1257,403,1149]" captionTargetId="figure@11.[302,1285,388,1178]" captionTargetPageId="11" captionText="FIGURES 8 A – F. Pisidium vile, anatomy. A, B. Lateral views of left (38) and right (39) inner mantle border showing siphonal and inner radial mantle muscles. C. Distribution of scars of inner radial mantle muscles. D. Inner view of inner demibranch showing position of developing brood sac. E. Left nephridium, dorsolateral view. F. Nephridia, dorsal view. (al: ascending lamellae; bs: brood sac; dl: descending lamellae; dln: dorsal lobe of nephridium; irm: inner radial mantle muscles; irms: scars of inner radial mantle muscles; ll: lateral loop of nephridium; pa: posterior adductor muscle; pl: pallial line; sr 1: anal siphon retractor; sr 2: retractor muscles corresponding to the lacking inhalant opening)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/174355/files/figure.png" pageId="9" pageNumber="42">
Fig. 
<number box="[676,691,1311,1337]" pageId="9" pageNumber="42" value="8.0">8</number>
C
</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="9.[264,1323,470,1897]" pageId="9" pageNumber="42">
<emphasis box="[312,378,1351,1376]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="42">Gills:</emphasis>
Only inner demibranch present. Developing brood pouch occupying the upper part of the inner demibranch, formed by 
<number box="[749,778,1391,1417]" pageId="9" pageNumber="42" value="12.0">12</number>
(in a 
<quantity box="[850,941,1391,1417]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.4" pageId="9" pageNumber="42" unit="mm" value="2.4">2.4 mm</quantity>
long specimen) to 
<number box="[1170,1199,1391,1417]" pageId="9" pageNumber="42" value="17.0">17</number>
(in a 
<quantity metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.75" pageId="9" pageNumber="42" unit="mm" value="2.75">2.75 mm</quantity>
long specimen) filaments (
<figureCitation box="[642,739,1431,1457]" captionStart="FIGURES 8 A – F" captionStartId="11.[264,382,1168,1192]" captionTargetBox="[315,1257,403,1149]" captionTargetId="figure@11.[302,1285,388,1178]" captionTargetPageId="11" captionText="FIGURES 8 A – F. Pisidium vile, anatomy. A, B. Lateral views of left (38) and right (39) inner mantle border showing siphonal and inner radial mantle muscles. C. Distribution of scars of inner radial mantle muscles. D. Inner view of inner demibranch showing position of developing brood sac. E. Left nephridium, dorsolateral view. F. Nephridia, dorsal view. (al: ascending lamellae; bs: brood sac; dl: descending lamellae; dln: dorsal lobe of nephridium; irm: inner radial mantle muscles; irms: scars of inner radial mantle muscles; ll: lateral loop of nephridium; pa: posterior adductor muscle; pl: pallial line; sr 1: anal siphon retractor; sr 2: retractor muscles corresponding to the lacking inhalant opening)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/174355/files/figure.png" pageId="9" pageNumber="42">
Fig. 
<number box="[700,714,1431,1457]" pageId="9" pageNumber="42" value="8.0">8</number>
D
</figureCitation>
). Between five and 
<number box="[985,1013,1431,1457]" pageId="9" pageNumber="42" value="11.0">11</number>
embryos per pouch were found.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="9.[264,1323,470,1897]" pageId="9" pageNumber="42">
<emphasis box="[312,461,1511,1536]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="42">Nephridium:</emphasis>
Of the closed 
<typeStatus box="[641,694,1511,1537]" pageId="9" pageNumber="42">type</typeStatus>
, with broad and rectangular dorsal lobe (
<figureCitation box="[1190,1314,1511,1537]" captionStart="FIGURES 8 A – F" captionStartId="11.[264,382,1168,1192]" captionTargetBox="[315,1257,403,1149]" captionTargetId="figure@11.[302,1285,388,1178]" captionTargetPageId="11" captionText="FIGURES 8 A – F. Pisidium vile, anatomy. A, B. Lateral views of left (38) and right (39) inner mantle border showing siphonal and inner radial mantle muscles. C. Distribution of scars of inner radial mantle muscles. D. Inner view of inner demibranch showing position of developing brood sac. E. Left nephridium, dorsolateral view. F. Nephridia, dorsal view. (al: ascending lamellae; bs: brood sac; dl: descending lamellae; dln: dorsal lobe of nephridium; irm: inner radial mantle muscles; irms: scars of inner radial mantle muscles; ll: lateral loop of nephridium; pa: posterior adductor muscle; pl: pallial line; sr 1: anal siphon retractor; sr 2: retractor muscles corresponding to the lacking inhalant opening)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/174355/files/figure.png" pageId="9" pageNumber="42">
Fig. 
<number box="[1247,1261,1511,1537]" pageId="9" pageNumber="42" value="8.0">8</number>
E, F
</figureCitation>
) and lateral loop visible from dorsal view.
</paragraph>
